---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Callout from '../../components/Callout.astro';

export const title = "Scarborough Cannabis Guide";
---

<Layout 
  title="Scarborough Cannabis Guide | Maine Dispensary Guide" 
  description="Understanding the cannabis business regulations in Scarborough, Maine. Local retail prohibition, cultivation opportunities, and zoning analysis."
  heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500916434205-0c77489c6cf7?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=1200&h=400"
>
  <article>
    <div class="article-header">
      <h1>Scarborough Cannabis Guide</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Navigating the cannabis industry in Scarborough, Maine</p>
    </div>

    <Callout title="Regulatory Notice: Retail Prohibition" type="tip">
      As of March 2026, **Scarborough does not permit adult-use (recreational) or medical retail marijuana stores.** While the town has opted into cultivation and manufacturing, retail storefronts are strictly prohibited. Entrepreneurs looking for retail locations should explore nearby <a href="/guides/south-portland-dispensary-guide/">South Portland</a> or <a href="/guides/old-orchard-beach-dispensary-guide/">Old Orchard Beach</a>.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Scarborough is one of Maine's premier coastal communities, offering a high quality of life and a robust business environment. In the cannabis sector, Scarborough has taken a specialized approach by opting into the "production" side of the industry while maintaining a clear prohibition on retail storefronts. This makes Scarborough a prime destination for large-scale <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-cultivation-guide/">cultivators</a> and manufacturers who need sophisticated industrial space.</p>
    </section>

    <Callout title="Production Powerhouse" type="passion">
      Scarborough's industrial zones are perfectly suited for state-of-the-art cultivation and lab facilities. If your passion is the science of the plant—breeding, extraction, or testing—Scarborough offers the professional infrastructure and affluent community support to build a world-class production brand.
    </Callout>

    <section>
      <h2>Current Status: What is Allowed?</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cultivation</strong> - Scarborough allows adult-use cultivation in specific industrial zones.</li>
        <li><strong>Manufacturing</strong> - Product manufacturing and extraction are permitted.</li>
        <li><strong>Testing Facilities</strong> - The town has opted into allowing cannabis testing labs.</li>
        <li><strong>Retail Storefronts</strong> - ❌ **PROHIBITED.** No retail stores (Adult-use or Medical) are allowed.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Scarborough Market Snapshot</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Factor</th><th>Assessment</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Population</td><td>20,000+ (Affluent demographic)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Retail Opt-In</td><td>No (Prohibited)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Production Opt-In</td><td>Yes (Cultivation, Mfg, Testing)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Zoning</td><td>Industrial zones only</td></tr>
          <li>Access</td><td>I-95, Route 1, I-295</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>The Scarborough Strategy</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>**Focus on B2B:** Build a <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-cultivation-guide/">cultivation brand</a> that supplies the nearby retail hubs.</li>
        <li>**Lab Opportunities:** Scarborough is an ideal location for <a href="/guides/maine-cannabis-product-testing-guide/">testing facilities</a> due to its proximity to southern Maine's largest markets.</li>
        <li>**Industrial Synergy:** Leverage the town's existing professional services and logistics networks.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="further-reading">
      <h2>Further Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://www.maine.gov/dafs/ocp/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Maine Office of Cannabis Policy (OCP)</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.scarboroughmaine.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Town of Scarborough Official Site</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="disclaimer">
      <p><em>This guide is for informational purposes only. Municipal ordinances are strictly enforced. Consult with the Scarborough Planning Department before pursuing a production license.</em></p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  article { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .article-header { margin-bottom: 2rem; padding-bottom: 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .subtitle { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-text-light); }
  section { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  section h2, section h3 { margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  section h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1rem 0; }
  th, td { padding: 0.75rem; text-align: left; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  th { background: var(--color-background); }
  ul { padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .disclaimer { background: #fff3cd; border: 1px solid #ffc107; padding: 1rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
  .further-reading { background: rgba(88, 129, 87, 0.05); padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 1rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .further-reading h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; }
</style>
